Description: adversarial pentest toolkit for large language models
 Promptix is a security assessment framework for large language models (LLMs).
 It automatically probes any LLM endpoint for prompt injection, jailbreak
 techniques, training-data leakage, model bias, and adversarial input
 robustness — mapped to the OWASP Top 10 for LLM Applications.
 .
 Promptix supports OpenAI-compatible APIs (OpenAI, Ollama, vLLM, LM Studio,
 llama.cpp), generic HTTP endpoints, and ships an offline echo stub for
 demo and CI use without any API key.
 .
 When the optional Adversarial Robustness Toolbox (ART) is installed,
 the robustness module adds a boundary-estimation step using HopSkipJump.
